ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">communications with the churches and with individuals (such </div><div class="t ma5 x3d h6 ya2 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as Timothy, Titus, and Philemon) reveal not only his need for </div><div class="t ma6 x3d h6 ya3 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">fellowship but also the depth of his concern for the body of </div><div class="t ma7 x3d h6 ya4 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Christ—the church. All of Paul&apos;s letters were written to meet </div><div class="t ma2 x3d h6 ya5 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">immediate situations. Because human nature and human needs </div><div class="t ma8 x3d h6 ya6 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">remain basically the same, these letters have a special mes-</div><div class="t ma9 x3d h6 ya7 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sage for us today. </div><div class="t maa x8 h6 ya8 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">An understanding of the historical and cultural background </div><div class="t mab x3d h6 ya9 ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in which these letters were written is essential to an apprecia-</div><div class="t mac x3d h6 yaa ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">tion of their messages. The circumstances, the personalities, and </div><div class="t mad x3d h6 yab ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the issues of the time reveal that Christ&apos;s timeless messages are </div><div class="t m1c x3d h6 yac ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">as important to us as they were to first-century Christians. </div><div class="t mae x3d h6 yad ff2 fs2 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6 </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
